From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 16:39:42 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Add Claude Sonnet 5 record-extraction stage; rebuild Case
 Profile on it
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The term matcher proves a term appears in a document. A Plaintiff Fact Sheet
needs the dose, the route, the prescriber, the injection dates, the ICD-10, the
test that confirmed the diagnosis — fields, not keyword hits. The old Case
Profile tried to synthesise those from term frequency and a regex date scan over
±8-word evidence windows, which produced plausible-looking, unsound output:
proximity-guessed exposure dates, mid-sentence "verbatim" quotes, the same
causation sentence listed three times, no demographics, and no respect for
reviewer decisions or routing.

Extraction stage (pipeline/casepipe/extract_records.py, records.py):
- One Sonnet call per document over page-tagged text — the same word stream the
  matcher sees. The model never sees the PDF, so it cannot read what OCR could
  not produce.
- Every record must carry a verbatim quote and the page it came from. The quote
  is then located in that page's word stream; if it cannot be found, the record
  is discarded as a hallucination and counted. 5/5 fabricated test records were
  rejected, including a plausible fake row in a real injection table.
- A located quote yields highlight rects and the OCR confidence of the words
  actually quoted, for free.
- confidence = model_certainty x grounding x page_ocr_conf x source_factor,
  routed on the matcher's existing 0.85/0.60 thresholds. The 47%-confidence
  urgent-care fax escalates every record on it regardless of how sure the model
  claims to be.
- record_spec.json is the single source of truth (model, prompt, tool schema,
  thresholds). Both runtimes import it; lib/record-grounding.ts is a port of
  records.py verified to reproduce its numbers exactly across all 103 records —
  the same relationship client-pipeline.ts has to match.py.
- Raw model output is committed to fixtures/extractions/, so --raw replays a run
  with no API call: grounding and routing changes are reviewable without
  re-billing.

Fixtures: 103 records grounded, 0 ungrounded (79 auto / 16 review / 8 escalated).

Case Profile (lib/case-profile.ts, app/(frontend)/profile):
- Rebuilt on records: identity, exposure, administration log, diagnosis
  timeline, causation, treatment, providers, ruled-out findings.
- Nothing is asserted without a citation to document, page, and quote.
- Nothing is silently chosen: real conflicts surface (Depo-Provera's last
  injection 07/19/2022 vs formal discontinuation 01/05/2023; ibuprofen 600mg
  prescribed vs 400mg taken). Cosmetic differences are reconciled quietly —
  a flag that cries wolf is worse than no flag.
- Field-level approve/reject writes through to every backing record; rejected
  fields never reach the export.
- The .docx is a real draft PFS with a "Verification required before filing"
  appendix listing every low-confidence extraction and unresolved conflict.
  Export now writes an audit event.

Also: live extraction route (app/api/extract-records) wired into Upload &
Process, with the ungrounded-rejection count shown on screen; case_records table
+ seed SQL; README.
